<TITLE> Chhatra Union leader Manabendra sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 24 (bdnews24.com) A Dhaka court Monday sent Bangladesh Chhatra Union leader Manabendra Deb to jail in a case that involves an arson attack on an army vehicle in the August rioting. Investigating officer Golam Rabbani Sunday asked the court to record Manab's statement. But he refused to testify when brought to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka Monday. Magistrate Hasan Sarowar then sent him to jail. Corporal Kamrul Hasan filed the case with Shahbagh Police Station on Aug 26 against unnamed people in connection with the arson attack. Joint forces arrested Manabendra, president of the Dhaka University chapter of Chhatra Union, at his home in Tantibazar on Sept 17. He was taken on a four-day remand the same day. Shahbagh police took him on a three-day remand on Sept 22 in a second round. bdnews24.com/pb/
